Clicking on a tab panel header in the issue view switches the tab panel you're viewing, but it also scrolls your browser back up to the top of the page, which can be annoying if the issue has a lot of content above the tab panels.  If you click on a tab panel, you most likely want to view that information immediately, so you end up scrolling down each time.

It seems like a pretty trivial change (I've attached the perforce diff I used for implementing this).

This task is a place holder of findings from examining 1 days worth of JAC logging

sysout-2009-05-26_040059.log


I think part of the problem is that stack traces get generated by default on

{code}
log.error(msg,exception)
{code}

Its like maybe we need a different coding idiom of

{code}
log.error(msg)
if (log.isDebugEnabled())
{
   log.debug(msg,exception)
}
{code}

And that we people can turn on the debug level if stuff is to be debugged for real.

I do a search from the simple navigator where I choose resolution = unresolved, and Status = In progress.

I get take to the Advanced Search screen and see this JQL:
{code}
resolution = EMPTY AND status = 3
{code}

JIRA won't let me switch to simple editing unless I remove the status clause.

